##Donald Trump wasn't worried about infection. "It was just an act. " 

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Sinembo, thepaper.cn

US President Donald Trump is one of the few people who has publicly dismissed the new crown disease: Even the announcement of such a draconian measure as a travel ban on Europe could not resist adding, "in fact, the risk is low. ".

But this may be a superficial phenomenon, different sources suggest that the president, a severe Germaphobe who calls himself "germ-phobic, " is secretly afraid of contracting the new coronavirus. In public, he insisted on playing down the risks, partly out of fear that panic would hit the economy and drag him into re-election.

Donald Trump is running for another four years in office, and a strong economy is what keeps him in the race for the Democratic nomination. And with a new outbreak of pneumonia in the United States, Donald Trump is under increasing pressure.

He says he's fine. He's scared in private

Donald Trump's approach to the new coronavirus ran counter to public and media opinion from the start. Despite rapid increases in the number of confirmed cases over the past few weeks and repeated warnings from public health experts, Donald Trump has repeatedly said there is nothing to worry about.

Donald Trump has repeatedly called on the American public to "just think of the new coronavirus as the flu, " a line he repeated on twitter on Monday. He is also pinning his hopes of containing the outbreak on the weather, which he recently predicted would disappear with the heat in April.

Even as the new coronavirus has entered Washington and is closing in on the White House, Donald Trump appears to be "calm. ".

So far this week, at least five members of Congress, including Donald Trump's new appointee, White House Chief of Staff Meadows, have isolated themselves for having been in close contact with a clinician while attending the conservative political action conference (CPAC) late last month.

Donald Trump also attended the event, but was said to have had no direct contact with the person who was diagnosed. However, two of the five self sequestered lawmakers have recently been in close contact with Donald Trump. One of them had been aboard Air Force One with Donald Trump.

Despite intense concern that Donald Trump might be infected, the President of the Chamber of Deputies of Tunisia Pelosi called for Donald Trump to be tested, but the White House insisted that Donald Trump was in excellent health and did not need to be tested for the virus. Asked about the situation, Donald Trump said on the 7th, "I'm not scared at all. "

But that may not be true. An article in Vanity Fair on March 11th revealed that many White House aides say Donald Trump is actually secretly terrified of a new coronavirus. News of Donald Trump's fear of contracting the new coronavirus had already spread to the White House, the article said.

Trump told an aide last week that he feared reporters were deliberately spreading the new coronavirus to infect him on Air Force One, the report said, citing a source. To this end, Donald Trump not only asked the secret service to develop a screening program, but also asked that anyone with cough symptoms be barred from entering the White House.

Donald Trump denied the claim on twitter, and a White House spokesman quoted Donald Trump as calling it "completely false news. ".

However, the CNN quoted a source close to Donald Trump as saying on the 13th that Donald Trump was indeed very worried. The source said Donald Trump was concerned about confidantes admitting that he did have concerns about contact with people infected with the new coronavirus, including Brazilian officials who confirmed the infection after returning from a recent visit to the United States. "He was worried about everyone he saw, including the Brazilians, " the source said.

A Brazilian press officer who met with President Donald Trump during a visit to the United States confirmed the diagnosis of new crown pneumonia. Still, Donald Trump insisted on Friday that he was not worried about his health, saying he was just sitting next to him for a while.

Donald Trump's private fear of the new coronavirus is not surprising. Many people around Donald Trump had already confirmed that he had always been a serious GERMOPHOBE, and years earlier Donald Trump had declared himself a "GERM-PHOBIC" .

US media have previously revealed that Donald Trump is a keen hand cleaner and generally avoids shaking hands after speeches and rallies, even when shaking hands he immediately disinfects them with hand sanitizer. He would even ask visitors to the White House to wash their hands in the bathroom of a nearby Oval Office. He hated to see a sick man appear before him, and would quickly dismiss an assistant who coughed and sneezed in front of him.

In fact, according to Rep. Matt Gates, who has quarantined himself, Donald Trump has taken a number of precautions recently, including frequent use of hand sanitizer.

The Washington Post reported Monday that Donald Trump's White House physician, Sean Conley, had recently begun attending certain meetings at the White House, and that cleaning operations inside the White House were more frequent than usual, people with flu-like symptoms were asked not to enter the White House because they "could infect leaders of the free world" .

Black Swan on the road to re-election

In analysing Donald Trump's response to the outbreak, the Vanity Fair article argued that Donald Trump was in effect treating a public health crisis as a media war. "He [ Donald Trump ] is trying to control a narrative he can't control, " a White House official said

The article notes that the crisis fits into Donald Trump's long held worldview that the media are always gathering stories to bring him down. The new crown disease is one such example, and Donald Trump has chosen a response he is familiar with -- a response he calls "false news" .

Another, more important, reason may be his fear that panic will hit the economy. Donald Trump is keen to boast about his economic record, which is key to his re election bid in November. For a second term, the deeply GERMAPHOBIC president would have preferred to play down the epidemic.

As the BBC pointed out in a recent article, the approval ratings and stock market data are something Donald Trump keeps a close eye on. Donald Trump expects his approval ratings to soar if the stock market soars, and he will be re elected in November. He has boosted the market almost every four days since taking office by tweeting.

From the start, The New York Times reported, there was disagreement within the White House about how much truth to disclose to the public. Despite early warnings from U.S. health officials and urging the White House to take action, Donald Trump feared disrupting financial markets and sparking panic.

Under pressure from the Donald Trump, many White House officials are too afraid to voice conflicting views for fear of angering Donald Trump. Defense Secretary Esper also warned the military not to make decisions that would conflict with President Donald Trump's message.

Last month, U.S. health officials worried about the outbreak took advantage of trump's flight back from India to warn that community transmission of the new coronavirus in the United States was inevitable, the news quickly triggered a sell-off in the US stock market. According to The New York Times, Donald Trump was furious. He telephoned Health Minister Adjara Autonomous Republic as soon as he stepped off the plane, accusing the warning of scaring people.

But Everything Donald Trump has done seems to have backfired. He told the public not to worry about the epidemic passing, but the number of confirmed cases in the United States was growing faster and faster; he said the United States was well prepared, only to have vice president Michel Pens√©e turn around and admit that the kits simply weren't enough. Republicans close to the White House say his optimism is fundamentally divorced from reality, exacerbating the epidemic.

As a result, the epidemic did not end as quickly as Donald Trump had hoped, and the stock market did not stop its decline, Americans became increasingly dissatisfied with Donald Trump's handling of the epidemic, indeed, some US media have accused Donald Trump of being the biggest obstacle to containing the outbreak.

Donald Trump used to have a commanding lead in this year's election, but the epidemic has left his re election prospects uncertain. The Washington Post reports that White House officials are increasingly concerned that the rapidly spreading outbreak is a "black swan event" that could derail Donald Trump's re-election bid.
